column3: What are the company’s human rights and environmental policies?
column4: What are the company’s vendor/supplier policies covering human rights and environmental standards across the supply chain?
column5: Publishes the company’s human rights and environmental management procedures
column6: Publishes a strategic plan towards progressively improving human rights and environmental impacts
column7: Publishes an annual sustainability or corporate social responsibility report that is audited or verified by an independent third party
column8: Publicly discloses contact details for the department the company that has responsibility for human rights and environmental issues
column9: Publicly discloses the company board member or board committee accountable for human rights and environmental issues
column10: Publicly acknowledges how the company prioritises money spent on managing and implementing CSR and sustainability activities
column11: Publishes how the company incorporates human rights and environmental performance into purchasing practices
column14: Publishes suppliers of raw materials such as fibres, hides, rubber, dyes, metals, etc.
column15: Publicly discloses human rights and environmental due diligence processes, outcomes and what brand is doing to remediate any issues identified.
column16: Publicly discloses how the company assesses implementation of its supply chain policies by facility
column17: Publicly discloses findings from its facility-level assessments
column18: Publicly discloses description and status of the remediation process
column19: Publicly discloses how the company ensures human rights and environmental grievances from employees and workers are captured and addressed
